2015-07~07
http://www.bangkokpost.com/news/asia/626088/china-says-4-killed-in-crackdown-on-uighurs-fleeing-country

Bangkok Post
This file photo taken on April 15 shows Uighur women wearing headscarfs while shopping at a bazaar in Hotan, in China's western Xinjiang region. Chinese police said they have shot dead four militants and found 553 Uighurs attempting to flee the country since last year.
The report comes as China steps ups efforts to bolster its claims that some of the 109 Uighurs deported from Thailand back to China last week posed a security threat, amid global concern about their well-being.

